The evidence with the title 'More and more Americans are outside the labor force entirely. Who ... ' says Nov 14, 2014  ... More than 92 million Americans last month were considered outside the labor force entirely .  ... According to the october jobs report , more than 92 million Americans — 37 % of the civilian population aged 16 and over — are neither employed nor unemployed , but fall in the category of “ not in the labor force . 
